WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:08.704
- Previously, on "Happy!"...
- [groans]

00:08.747 --> 00:09.748
- New private school?

00:09.792 --> 00:11.359
8,000 per quarter.

00:11.402 --> 00:13.361
Believe it or not,
I'm counting on Nick.

00:13.404 --> 00:15.276
[both laughing]

00:15.319 --> 00:18.322
- The kids will wait here
until you sound the horn.

00:18.366 --> 00:20.150
Then they run out
to the eastern meadow.

00:20.194 --> 00:22.848
- [muffled hollering]

00:22.892 --> 00:26.156
- I have removed
all of the skin from your body.

00:26.200 --> 00:28.767
I will determine
your time of death

00:28.811 --> 00:30.726
down to the hour.

00:30.769 --> 00:33.163
- Call the goddamn Feds.

00:33.207 --> 00:35.209
Take the goddamn deal.

00:35.252 --> 00:36.688
- I--I've seen it happen
a thousand times.

00:36.732 --> 00:38.603
Guys can't take the pressure.
They just crack.

00:38.647 --> 00:40.779
- Let's go ahead
and kill the idiot.

00:40.823 --> 00:43.826
[all grunting]

00:43.869 --> 00:45.741
- You're Blue's
personal lawyer, Geno.

00:45.784 --> 00:48.439
I would love to know what you
and Sonny had to talk about.

00:48.483 --> 00:49.745
- He's got blackmail
on everyone.

00:49.788 --> 00:51.268
It's on video tape.

00:51.312 --> 00:53.227
He knows what people wish for.
The dark stuff.

00:53.270 --> 00:54.793
The stuff they don't even tell
their shrinks about.

00:54.837 --> 00:56.447
- Tell me where
he keeps the tapes.

00:56.491 --> 00:59.320
[suspenseful music]

00:59.363 --> 01:04.238
♪

01:05.935 --> 01:09.286
[choir singing]

01:09.330 --> 01:15.292
♪ Glory receive us all, Lord

01:15.336 --> 01:18.600
♪ My Father crucified

01:18.643 --> 01:25.433
♪ Has brought to life
his own ♪

01:25.476 --> 01:27.304
- I thought they were
only supposed to do that

01:27.348 --> 01:28.740
on Ash Wednesday?

01:28.784 --> 01:30.699
- It's kind of
a regular thing here.

01:30.742 --> 01:33.441
- Some girls need a lot
of repenting.

01:33.484 --> 01:35.443
[choir singing]

01:35.486 --> 01:36.835
- What's the matter?

01:36.879 --> 01:39.142
Haven't you ever been
to mass before?

01:39.186 --> 01:41.536
- No.
- That explains it.

01:41.579 --> 01:42.841
- Explains what?

01:42.885 --> 01:44.452
- Why Santa picked you.

01:44.495 --> 01:45.931
You have sin in your heart.

01:45.975 --> 01:50.153
♪

01:50.197 --> 01:52.329
- Remember that you are dust.

01:52.373 --> 01:56.203
[slowed speech]
And to dust you shall return.

01:56.246 --> 01:58.292
- [echoing]
This is gonna pinch.

01:58.335 --> 02:00.337
Just a little.
[wheezing laughter]

02:00.381 --> 02:01.730
You could be little forever.

02:01.773 --> 02:03.514
[drill whirring]

02:03.558 --> 02:04.907
- [shrieks]
- [hollers]

02:04.950 --> 02:08.171
My thumb!
You broke my fucking thumb!

02:08.215 --> 02:09.477
You goddamn little--

02:09.520 --> 02:12.175
[ding]

02:12.219 --> 02:14.569
- Shot of bourbon,
shot of tequila,

02:14.612 --> 02:17.833
Bloody Mary back,
and a pineapple juice

02:17.876 --> 02:19.661
for the lady.
[clicks tongue]

02:19.704 --> 02:22.664
[jazzy music playing]

02:22.707 --> 02:25.232
- [throaty sigh]

02:25.275 --> 02:27.973
That ass is thicker
than a bowl of porridge.

02:28.017 --> 02:29.671
- "That ass"
is someone's daughter.

02:29.714 --> 02:32.326
- Uh-huh.
Somebody's mama, too, I bet.

02:32.369 --> 02:34.328
- All right, Le Dic, what
the hell are we doing here?

02:34.371 --> 02:35.851
You know I'm trying
to stay sober.

02:35.894 --> 02:37.331
Make changes in my life.

02:37.374 --> 02:38.854
- I can see that.

02:38.897 --> 02:40.638
Moved out of that
apartment-sized Petri dish

02:40.682 --> 02:42.205
you called a home.

02:42.249 --> 02:43.598
You got yourself
a summer shirt that makes

02:43.641 --> 02:46.862
you look like
an unemployed homosexual.

02:46.905 --> 02:48.951
Fatherhood becomes you, Nicky.

02:48.994 --> 02:50.953
How's the missy?

02:50.996 --> 02:52.520
- Hey, Hailey's great,
you know.

02:52.563 --> 02:54.217
She's starting her first day
at her new school--

02:54.261 --> 02:56.219
- You sound like
a goddamn wet nurse.

02:56.263 --> 02:58.265
I don't give a fuck
about your daughter's school.

02:58.308 --> 03:00.919
I'm here to talk shop.
I got a job for you.

03:00.963 --> 03:02.486
[whistle blowing]
- Flag on the play.

03:02.530 --> 03:05.446
This is a direct violation
of the bylaws.

03:05.489 --> 03:06.751
"Consorting with
a criminal element."

03:06.795 --> 03:09.537
- I wanna thank you...

03:09.580 --> 03:13.018
for your offer,
but as I told you before...

03:13.062 --> 03:15.412
I'm out of the game.
- Atta boy, Nick.

03:15.456 --> 03:18.894
- No. You told Nick
no killing, maiming, battery,

03:18.937 --> 03:20.852
bribes, blackmail, fraud,

03:20.896 --> 03:23.377
kidnapping, carjacking,
or arson.

03:23.420 --> 03:26.815
- Yeah. I had to stop at nine
on account of your handicap.

03:26.858 --> 03:29.513
♪

03:29.557 --> 03:31.602
- The job I got for you...

03:31.646 --> 03:33.343
is a simple B and E.

03:33.387 --> 03:35.737
- Bacon and eggs?
Sign me up!

03:35.780 --> 03:37.391
- "Breaking and entering,"
you say?

03:37.434 --> 03:39.001
- I do say.
- So why are you talking to me?

03:39.044 --> 03:40.568
There are plenty
of "B and E" guys out there.

03:40.611 --> 03:42.265
- There sure are,
but none as good as you.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.614
- Oh, stop with the flattery.

03:43.658 --> 03:46.791
- I can't help it,
you're the best.

03:46.835 --> 03:47.923
- I am pretty good.

03:47.966 --> 03:49.925
- No, not "pretty good."

03:49.968 --> 03:51.970
The best.
Like James Bond.

03:52.014 --> 03:53.755
Only better
'cause you're American.

03:53.798 --> 03:55.974
- All right,
everything you say is true.

03:57.628 --> 04:00.283
Even still, fact remains
I got a daughter now.

04:00.327 --> 04:01.589
Can't do it.

04:01.632 --> 04:02.807
- It pays, Nicky.

04:02.851 --> 04:05.070
2K.
- Don't do it, Nick.

04:05.114 --> 04:06.768
I know we need the money
for Hailey's school

04:06.811 --> 04:08.683
but it's not worth your soul.

04:08.726 --> 04:12.600
- My soul ain't worth
$2,000.

04:12.643 --> 04:13.644
- Yes!

04:13.688 --> 04:17.779
- My soul is worth
$3,200.

04:17.822 --> 04:19.650
- Hmm.
- Final offer.

04:19.694 --> 04:21.739
- [wailing] No!

04:23.393 --> 04:24.960
- Details in here.

04:25.003 --> 04:28.833
Dead drop's at the shipyard,
1600 hours.

04:30.357 --> 04:31.619
Go with God.

04:31.662 --> 04:34.317
- You broke
Father Eddie's thumb

04:34.361 --> 04:36.014
in two places.

04:36.058 --> 04:38.539
What do you have to say
for yourself?

04:38.582 --> 04:39.844
- It was an accident.

04:39.888 --> 04:43.065
- [imitates buzzer]
Wrong answer.

04:43.108 --> 04:46.329
How old are you, Hailey?
- Almost 11.

04:46.373 --> 04:48.113
- Well, that's practically
a grown-up.

04:48.157 --> 04:52.640
I hold grown-ups accountable
for their muck-ups,

04:52.683 --> 04:58.646
but Jesus gives us
another option: repentance.

05:00.778 --> 05:02.824
- I'm sorry.

05:02.867 --> 05:04.956
- Better.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.828
Oh, there, now.

05:06.871 --> 05:09.831
First day at a new school.
No friends.

05:09.874 --> 05:11.746
You feel isolated.

05:11.789 --> 05:13.051
It's only natural.

05:13.095 --> 05:15.358
Here.

05:15.402 --> 05:16.881
Read this.

05:16.925 --> 05:20.407
[austere music]

05:20.450 --> 05:23.932
"Zipporah cut off
her son's foreskin

05:23.975 --> 05:25.934
and touched
Moses' feet with it."

05:25.977 --> 05:28.937
- Oops! Wrong place.
Hang on.

05:32.201 --> 05:33.768
Proverbs.

05:35.639 --> 05:38.860
- "Those who trust
in themselves are fools,

05:38.903 --> 05:41.950
but those who walk in wisdom
are kept safe."

05:41.993 --> 05:46.737
- That means you mustn't
act out in fear, Hailey.

05:46.781 --> 05:49.914
It may seem we're all alone.

05:49.958 --> 05:54.702
Nevertheless,
there's someone watching us.

05:54.745 --> 05:57.531
Protecting us.

05:57.574 --> 05:59.533
[phone dings]

05:59.576 --> 06:00.751
- Hmm.

06:00.795 --> 06:02.100
- I haven't seem you
smile like that

06:02.144 --> 06:04.146
since Bell Biv Devoe
made the big comeback.

06:04.189 --> 06:06.583
- I got a nice text,
that's all.

06:06.627 --> 06:09.064
- You got laid.
- Dr. Reddy, he can hear us.

06:09.107 --> 06:11.893
- [clicks tongue]
Out like a light.

06:11.936 --> 06:15.070
Now dish, sister.

06:15.113 --> 06:17.899
- I met somebody.
He's pretty great.

06:17.942 --> 06:20.902
- [giddy laugh] Okay, I've got
to drain the monkey,

06:20.945 --> 06:22.164
so I'll be right back.

06:22.207 --> 06:23.557
You rinse him out,

06:23.600 --> 06:25.472
and then I want
to hear everything.

06:25.515 --> 06:27.082
Okay? [chuckles]

06:27.125 --> 06:29.563
[upbeat synth music builds]

06:29.606 --> 06:30.868
[blows]

06:30.912 --> 06:33.915
[lengthy stretching noises]

06:33.958 --> 06:35.960
♪

06:36.004 --> 06:37.005
[woman speaking indistinctly]

06:37.048 --> 06:38.441
♪

06:38.485 --> 06:39.877
[echoing indistinctly]

06:39.921 --> 06:42.489
[alarm sounding]

06:42.532 --> 06:45.230
[water gushing]

06:45.274 --> 06:48.799
- [coughing, gagging]

06:51.759 --> 06:54.065
- Amanda, what are you doing?

06:54.109 --> 06:55.589
You're drowning him!

06:55.632 --> 06:57.852
What's the matter with you?
[exclaims]

06:57.895 --> 06:59.636
Timmy, wake up!

06:59.680 --> 07:01.116
[elegant music]

07:01.159 --> 07:04.467
- And so, for 40 days,
Jesus took to the desert

07:04.511 --> 07:06.251
with no food and no water.

07:06.295 --> 07:08.863
Nothing to distract him
from asking,

07:08.906 --> 07:11.692
"Am I ready to die
for what I believe in?"

07:11.735 --> 07:14.695
I'm only sorry
that my husband's hay fever

07:14.738 --> 07:17.785
was so severe
he couldn't be here today.

07:17.828 --> 07:19.264
But I know what he'd say

07:19.308 --> 07:22.050
to all these beautiful
boys and girls.

07:22.093 --> 07:24.966
"Imagine you were Jesus
starving in the desert

07:25.009 --> 07:26.620
for 40 years."

07:26.663 --> 07:29.579
Boo!
[crowd booing]

07:29.623 --> 07:31.668
♪

07:31.712 --> 07:34.976
- And now, imagine how happy
Jesus would be

07:35.019 --> 07:37.979
if he had all these
yummy treats to eat!

07:38.022 --> 07:40.111
Yay!

07:40.155 --> 07:43.854
[applause]

07:46.204 --> 07:48.859
Happy Easter!
Go, go, go.

07:48.903 --> 07:50.121
[dramatic music]

07:50.165 --> 07:53.124
[children cheering]

07:53.168 --> 08:00.218
♪

08:01.655 --> 08:04.701
[men vocalizing]

08:07.922 --> 08:10.968
[children clamoring]

08:23.328 --> 08:26.288
[tense music]

08:26.331 --> 08:28.203
♪

08:28.246 --> 08:29.552
- [hoarse gasp]

08:29.596 --> 08:31.641
[children shrieking]
- [gasps]

08:31.685 --> 08:35.079
[all gasping, chattering]

08:35.123 --> 08:38.561
[screams continue over TV]

08:39.344 --> 08:41.259
- [sighs]
I'd forgotten how much I love

08:41.303 --> 08:42.783
working with children.

08:42.826 --> 08:46.003
- Mm, those puffy white
marshmallow minds.

08:46.047 --> 08:48.049
So corruptible.

08:48.092 --> 08:50.747
You're a true gem, Smoothie.

08:50.791 --> 08:52.575
Although...

08:52.619 --> 08:54.142
never mind.

08:54.185 --> 08:55.883
- What?
- Nothing.

08:55.926 --> 08:58.929
- No, no, please.
I thrive on feedback.

08:58.973 --> 09:02.846
- Well, why dark chocolate
and not milk?

09:02.890 --> 09:04.065
I mean,
it's America's favorite.

09:04.108 --> 09:05.196
Kids can't get enough
of the stuff,

09:05.240 --> 09:06.894
and frankly, neither can I.

09:06.937 --> 09:09.331
- I'm afraid that
you would find the detail

09:09.374 --> 09:12.726
of my execution and planning
rather tedious.

09:12.769 --> 09:14.118
Be that as it may,

09:14.162 --> 09:16.120
dark chocolate has
a higher melting point

09:16.164 --> 09:17.644
than milk fat-based chocolate,

09:17.687 --> 09:19.254
and that assists
with cauterization.

09:19.297 --> 09:21.386
But more important--
and forgive me

09:21.430 --> 09:24.259
for my admittedly high-minded
flight of fancy--

09:24.302 --> 09:26.740
dark chocolate was the original
food of the gods.

09:26.783 --> 09:28.132
The Greeks called it marta--

09:28.176 --> 09:30.091
- Should have gone milk!

09:30.134 --> 09:31.266
Oh, well.

09:31.309 --> 09:32.920
On to the next.

09:32.963 --> 09:35.705
I have a few ideas
I'd like you to get started on.

09:35.749 --> 09:37.272
- I'm afraid
that isn't possible.

09:37.315 --> 09:39.317
I have something I need
to attend to this afternoon.

09:39.361 --> 09:40.667
- Really?

09:40.710 --> 09:43.104
May I ask what that is?

09:43.147 --> 09:44.845
- It's personal.

09:44.888 --> 09:47.369
- Smoothie, you have
no personal life.

09:47.412 --> 09:50.807
That's what makes you special.

09:50.851 --> 09:52.896
Little bunny eye.

09:52.940 --> 09:55.812
It's so cute.

09:55.856 --> 09:58.119
I want one.

09:58.162 --> 10:01.296
[blows raspberry, laughs]
I'm just joshing ya!

10:01.339 --> 10:03.907
You little so-and-so!
[laughing]

10:03.951 --> 10:05.343
I don't.

10:05.387 --> 10:07.432
You, take the afternoon,
all right?

10:07.476 --> 10:09.652
Company morale,
that's what I say.

10:09.696 --> 10:13.351
Bright-eyed and cotton-tailed
tomorrow, Smoothie!

10:13.395 --> 10:16.790
♪ The show must go on

10:16.833 --> 10:19.662
[telephone ringing, beeps]

10:19.706 --> 10:22.883
- Mr. Shine,
I have Kap Gostynski

10:22.926 --> 10:24.145
from the network?

10:24.188 --> 10:27.148
- More golf.

10:27.191 --> 10:29.933
- We were able to recover
four of the veneers.

10:29.977 --> 10:32.283
The remaining ones should pass
through his stool comfortably.

10:32.327 --> 10:33.981
Timmy's mom and dad say
they won't press charges.

10:34.024 --> 10:35.373
- Oh, thank heavens.

10:35.417 --> 10:36.984
- But they're not
happy campers, Amanda.

10:37.027 --> 10:38.681
Timmy almost drowned.

10:38.725 --> 10:40.727
I hate to do this, but--
- Doctor, please.

10:40.770 --> 10:43.991
- I think you need to take,
you know, some time off.

10:44.034 --> 10:47.211
Long time off.

10:49.257 --> 10:50.998
- You're firing me.

10:51.041 --> 10:53.000
- They're gonna kill me on Yelp
for this, Amanda.

10:53.043 --> 10:54.392
You don't give me any choice.

10:54.436 --> 10:57.352
- Yelp?
- [sighs]

10:57.395 --> 11:00.007
- You know...

11:00.050 --> 11:02.009
all right.

11:02.052 --> 11:04.185
Ten years.
- Hmm?

11:04.228 --> 11:06.361
- I did everything
I was supposed to do.

11:06.404 --> 11:08.145
Raised my little girl alone.

11:08.189 --> 11:09.756
It was never about me.

11:09.799 --> 11:12.846
I had to be strong for her,
for everyone.

11:12.889 --> 11:15.283
I was the rock.
- I love The Rock.

11:15.326 --> 11:17.198
- Now...

11:17.241 --> 11:19.722
there is something inside me,
you know?

11:19.766 --> 11:21.419
Something I don't understand.

11:21.463 --> 11:24.988
I think maybe I'm done being
everyone's bitch, Dr. Reddy.

11:25.032 --> 11:26.424
Maybe it's time
for someone else

11:26.468 --> 11:27.817
to pick things up for a change.

11:27.861 --> 11:30.037
- Okay, okay.
Real good.

11:30.080 --> 11:33.040
So if you can just
drop off your keys, that--

11:33.083 --> 11:35.172
- I don't understand
what's happening to me.

11:35.216 --> 11:38.872
- Oh, I'm so sorry, Amanda.
- [gasps]

11:38.915 --> 11:41.875
- Uh...

11:41.918 --> 11:44.225
- May I?
- Of course.

11:44.268 --> 11:46.531
[dark music]

11:46.575 --> 11:48.795
Hmm?

11:49.883 --> 11:52.059
- Feels like we're breaking
our promise to Hailey.

11:52.102 --> 11:53.495
- Well, we're not.
You heard Le Dic.

11:53.538 --> 11:55.889
We're not killing, maiming,
battering, bribing,

11:55.932 --> 11:57.978
blackmailing, defrauding,

11:58.021 --> 12:01.459
kidnapping, carjacking, or...

12:01.503 --> 12:03.026
- Arsoning.
- Exactly.

12:03.070 --> 12:05.507
So if it ain't on the list--
aww, crap.

12:05.550 --> 12:07.161
[thunder rumbling]

12:07.204 --> 12:08.989
"B and E" my balls.

12:09.032 --> 12:11.469
- But don't you ever feel bad
about taking peoples' stuff?

12:11.513 --> 12:14.168
Like--like, picture them
coming home and being like,

12:14.211 --> 12:15.909
"Whoa, where's my stuff?"

12:15.952 --> 12:18.912
- You know, I--I've been
grading you on a curve

12:18.955 --> 12:20.565
because, I mean, it's hard

12:20.609 --> 12:22.829
going from being a
little girl's imaginary friend

12:22.872 --> 12:24.874
to a big strong man's
imaginary friend,

12:24.918 --> 12:27.877
so let me be candid
about what I expect

12:27.921 --> 12:30.010
from somebody in your position.

12:30.053 --> 12:32.012
[suspenseful music]

12:32.055 --> 12:34.231
I don't want a mother.

12:34.275 --> 12:36.059
I don't want a wife.

12:36.103 --> 12:38.366
And I definitely do not want
a conscience.

12:38.409 --> 12:40.803
I had two of them three things.
It wasn't fun.

12:40.847 --> 12:43.937
But what I do want

12:43.980 --> 12:45.547
is a partner.

12:45.590 --> 12:47.375
Ah-nuh--

12:47.418 --> 12:50.030
[whispers] Silent partner.

12:50.073 --> 12:51.858
You know, someone who's gonna
be there when I need him

12:51.901 --> 12:53.816
and disappears when I don't.

12:53.860 --> 12:56.906
And I really feel that
that arrangement,

12:56.950 --> 12:58.603
gonna be beneficial
for both of us.

12:58.647 --> 13:01.128
- Right, this is all
for my benefit.

13:01.171 --> 13:03.043
- You see, right there.
Already, you're growing.

13:03.086 --> 13:05.349
That was sarcasm.
- I did sarcasm?

13:05.393 --> 13:07.874
- Yeah, you did--
and very well.

13:07.917 --> 13:09.179
Now flutter aside.

13:10.354 --> 13:13.575
- [gasps, exhales]

13:13.618 --> 13:16.099
Come in, noodle.

13:16.143 --> 13:19.320
You must be the new pool boy.

13:19.363 --> 13:22.062
My husband said
you were coming by.

13:22.105 --> 13:23.890
[door closes]

13:23.933 --> 13:25.630
- As I live and breathe.

13:25.674 --> 13:27.850
Happy, do you know
who that was?

13:28.938 --> 13:31.288
Bebe Debarge.
- Who?

13:31.332 --> 13:34.291
- Only the last
great movie start, that's who.

13:34.335 --> 13:36.990
"Operation Bim-bot,"
"Bride of The Blob,"

13:37.033 --> 13:40.515
She was the gym coach
in "Jacuzzi Police."

13:40.558 --> 13:42.386
Happy...

13:42.430 --> 13:44.258
we're robbing
Hollywood royalty.

13:44.301 --> 13:47.261
Ms. Debarge,
I'm your biggest fan.

13:47.304 --> 13:49.002
- Oh, do you know my work?

13:49.045 --> 13:51.656
- Oh, yes.
I owned the poster.

13:51.700 --> 13:53.354
You know, the one of you
in the gold bikini

13:53.397 --> 13:55.095
tossing your hair.

13:55.138 --> 13:56.923
- I'm sure I can't recall.

13:56.966 --> 13:59.403
- I used to admire it...

13:59.447 --> 14:02.493
nightly, if you know
what I mean.

14:02.537 --> 14:06.149
- Oh. I never tire of
hearing those stories.

14:06.193 --> 14:07.542
- Well, your husband's
a lucky man.

14:07.585 --> 14:10.371
- [laughs]
Hey, I'm a lucky woman.

14:10.414 --> 14:13.504
- Oh, are you.
Whoa, hey, whoa, whoa!

14:13.548 --> 14:17.987
- Holy sh--I mean, jeepers!
Poor guy.

14:18.031 --> 14:20.337
Imagine having to lug
that thing around all day.

14:20.381 --> 14:21.948
- I don't have
to imagine, Hap.

14:21.991 --> 14:23.471
- Uh, yeah, Nick.

14:23.514 --> 14:26.213
I've seen it.

14:26.256 --> 14:28.563
[groovy music]

14:28.606 --> 14:31.218
[music darkens]

14:31.261 --> 14:34.525
- Happy, Bebe's husband is...

14:34.569 --> 14:36.440
both: Sonny Shine!

14:39.922 --> 14:42.925
[machine beeping slowly]

14:42.969 --> 14:45.145
- [hoarse gasp]
[hollers]

14:45.188 --> 14:47.190
[stammering]

14:49.627 --> 14:52.674
[groaning]

14:57.331 --> 15:00.900
- Morning, Scaramucci.

15:00.943 --> 15:04.686
I was kite surfing
at Lake Atitlán in Guatemala

15:04.729 --> 15:06.906
over the holidays--

15:06.949 --> 15:09.560
superb conditions--

15:09.604 --> 15:13.695
so I didn't get the chance
to make your acquaintance.

15:14.565 --> 15:16.698
Warden Kilpatrick.

15:16.741 --> 15:19.744
- Seems like you've been
taking advantage

15:19.788 --> 15:22.878
of some of our
extracurricular activities.

15:23.923 --> 15:26.751
Sodomy.

15:26.795 --> 15:28.840
Sodomy.

15:28.884 --> 15:30.973
Murder.

15:31.017 --> 15:32.714
Sodomy.

15:32.757 --> 15:34.020
- [grunts]

15:36.239 --> 15:38.111
[stammering]
What happened?

15:38.154 --> 15:41.549
- I was gonna ask you
the same thing.

15:41.592 --> 15:43.986
I'm sure you understand,

15:44.030 --> 15:46.249
it's hard to imagine

15:46.293 --> 15:49.905
how one guy fought off
six members

15:49.949 --> 15:52.603
of the Dimitrov crime family.

15:52.647 --> 15:56.129
Vasiliev's skull was cracked
against the toilet seat...

15:56.172 --> 15:57.130
[blood dripping]

15:57.173 --> 15:59.697
Popov drowned.

15:59.741 --> 16:01.221
He had enough water
in his lungs

16:01.264 --> 16:02.962
to kill him ten times over.

16:03.005 --> 16:05.225
Ivanov...
- [screams]

16:05.268 --> 16:07.009
- The Lebdevs?

16:07.053 --> 16:09.925
- [grunting]
- [laughing] All of them...

16:09.969 --> 16:12.101
[imitates slicing]

16:12.145 --> 16:15.148
At the same time.

16:19.065 --> 16:22.155
- I... I don't know.

16:23.286 --> 16:25.593
- Amnesia's common
around here.

16:25.636 --> 16:27.029
[gate buzzes]

16:27.073 --> 16:30.206
You've got a visitor.
Your niece.

16:30.250 --> 16:31.816
[gate open]

16:31.860 --> 16:34.123
Maybe she can...

16:34.167 --> 16:37.170
jigger a memory or two loose.

16:37.213 --> 16:40.173
[foreboding music]

16:40.216 --> 16:42.958
You got five minutes,
Detective.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.743
- No, no, absolutely not.

16:45.787 --> 16:47.180
Get away, get away.

16:47.223 --> 16:48.964
- [childish voice]
But, Uncle Blue,

16:49.008 --> 16:52.402
I came all this way
to give you a hug.

16:52.446 --> 16:55.057
- Ah!

16:55.101 --> 16:56.754
- How's it going?
- [groans]

16:56.798 --> 16:58.060
- You want me
to fluff a pillow for you?

16:58.104 --> 16:59.105
Get you some ice chips?

16:59.148 --> 17:02.369
- Fuck you, Meredith!

17:02.412 --> 17:05.198
♪

17:05.241 --> 17:07.113
Like a daughter,
I treated you.

17:07.156 --> 17:08.984
- I know.

17:09.028 --> 17:11.378
I owe you big time.

17:11.421 --> 17:13.206
That's why I'm here.
- [slaps hand]

17:13.249 --> 17:15.860
How's the deal with the Feds
coming along?

17:15.904 --> 17:18.341
Not looking good, I hear.

17:18.385 --> 17:20.691
- Go to hell.

17:22.693 --> 17:25.000
Geno Sarcuzzi.

17:25.044 --> 17:27.350
I'm sure you recognize
Shine Tower.

17:27.394 --> 17:30.136
Attorney-client privilege
ain't what it used to be, huh?

17:30.179 --> 17:33.008
You trusted him.

17:33.052 --> 17:35.663
He belongs to Shine.

17:35.706 --> 17:38.970
I spoke to Geno earlier today.

17:39.014 --> 17:40.842
There's no deal, Blue.

17:40.885 --> 17:43.062
But...
- [hollers]

17:43.105 --> 17:46.152
- You can make one with me.

17:46.195 --> 17:49.459
Give me Sonny Shine.
- Oh, Merry.

17:49.503 --> 17:51.940
I would rather die in here

17:51.983 --> 17:56.118
than suffer the shame
of owing you anything.

17:56.162 --> 17:57.946
[yelps]
- Good luck with that.

17:57.989 --> 18:01.863
- [coughing, groaning]
Fuck!

18:01.906 --> 18:04.344
When I get out of here, Merry--
and I will--

18:04.387 --> 18:07.173
Ah! I'm gonna cut you
to ribbons!

18:07.216 --> 18:09.784
[coughing]
- Okay, just calm down.

18:09.827 --> 18:12.134
Get off!
Get off.

18:12.178 --> 18:15.094
- There, there, now.

18:15.137 --> 18:18.053
We're not going anywhere.

18:18.097 --> 18:20.055
[machine beeping quickly]

18:20.099 --> 18:21.056
[sinister music]

18:21.100 --> 18:23.102
- No, no, no--

18:23.145 --> 18:26.192
[groaning]

18:26.235 --> 18:27.454
♪

18:27.497 --> 18:30.196
- Ah!
[thudding]

18:30.239 --> 18:32.894
Ah--

18:36.202 --> 18:39.379
- Get on the ground!
Get on the ground now!

18:39.422 --> 18:42.730
- Even as Jesus hung
dying on the cross,

18:42.773 --> 18:44.732
he offered comfort to Dismas,

18:44.775 --> 18:46.908
the Penitent Thief
beside him.

18:46.951 --> 18:48.953
Leading him into
the kingdom of Heaven

18:48.997 --> 18:52.870
and making Saint Dismas
the first saint.

18:52.914 --> 18:54.959
Can anyone name
some other saints?

18:55.003 --> 18:56.831
- What about Saint Nick?

18:56.874 --> 18:58.354
- Nice, Dagny.

18:58.398 --> 19:01.140
- Sister, how did Saint Nick
become Santa Claus?

19:01.183 --> 19:02.967
- That's a good question.

19:03.011 --> 19:05.361
Saint Nick was the bishop
of Myrna,

19:05.405 --> 19:07.450
but he always took care
of the town's children.

19:07.494 --> 19:10.149
[children humming
"Jingle Bells"]

19:10.192 --> 19:12.368
- I know we all
love Christmas, girls,

19:12.412 --> 19:14.457
